WEBVTT

00:01.235 --> 00:03.737
YOU KNOW THE KIND OF GUY
WHO DOES NOTHING
BUT BAD THINGS...

00:03.771 --> 00:06.574
AND THEN WONDERS WHY
HIS LIFE SUCKS?

00:06.607 --> 00:11.145
WELL, THAT WAS ME.
EVERY TIME SOMETHIN' GOOD
HAPPENED TO ME,

00:11.179 --> 00:13.281
SOMETHIN' BAD
WAS ALWAYS WAITIN'
AROUND THE CORNER.

00:15.516 --> 00:17.118
KARMA.

00:17.151 --> 00:19.220
THAT'S WHEN I REALIZED
I HAD TO CHANGE.

00:20.754 --> 00:23.424
SO I MADE A LIST
OF EVERYTHING BAD
I'VE EVER DONE,

00:23.457 --> 00:26.394
AND, ONE BY ONE,
I'M GONNA MAKE UP
FOR ALL MY MISTAKES.

00:26.427 --> 00:28.362
I'M JUST TRYIN'
TO BE A BETTER PERSON.

00:28.396 --> 00:31.299
MY NAME IS EARL.

00:31.332 --> 00:35.303
[ Earl Narrating ]
EVER SINCE MY DIVORCE, WINNING
$100,000 IN THE LOTTERY...

00:35.336 --> 00:37.671
AND DISCOVERING
THE CONCEPT OF KARMA,

00:37.705 --> 00:39.640
I FEEL GREAT.

00:43.577 --> 00:45.413
[ Beeping ]

00:47.415 --> 00:51.219
AND THE MORE BAD THINGS
I CROSS OFF MY LIST,

00:51.252 --> 00:53.487
THE MORE KARMA REWARDS ME.

00:56.457 --> 00:58.292
CLEAN LIVIN'.

01:00.894 --> 01:03.631
RANDY, THERE'S SOMETHING
TO BE SAID ABOUT WAKING UP...

01:03.664 --> 01:07.135
AND FEELING
LIKE A GOOD PERSON.

01:07.168 --> 01:09.570
"U-R AN ASS."

01:09.603 --> 01:11.539
WHAT'D YOU SAY?

01:16.710 --> 01:19.180
JOY.

01:19.213 --> 01:21.882
WELL, IT WASN'T ME,
ALTHOUGH I DO AGREE
WITH YOUR CAR--

01:21.915 --> 01:24.352
YOU ARE AN ASS.

01:24.385 --> 01:27.855
- [ Kids Laughing ]
- UM, JOY?

01:27.888 --> 01:32.726
FINE! WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO,
CALL THE POLICE?

01:32.760 --> 01:36.364
PLEASE DO. I'D LIKE TO DISCUSS
WITH THEM WHERE YOU AND YOUR
BROTHER GOT THAT REFRIGERATOR.

01:36.397 --> 01:40.768
HOLD IT. DON'T CALL THE POLICE.
THEY STILL GOT MY PICTURE UP
OVER AT THE CIRCUIT CITY.

01:40.801 --> 01:43.204
LOOK, JUST LEAVE
MY STUFF ALONE, OKAY?

01:43.237 --> 01:46.174
HOW 'BOUT YOU GIVE ME
HALF THAT LOTTO MONEY, AND THEN
MAYBE I'LL LEAVE YOU ALONE?

01:46.207 --> 01:49.177
YOU KNOW I NEED
THAT MONEY SO I CAN MAKE UP
FOR THE THINGS ON MY LIST.

01:49.210 --> 01:51.445
YOU AND YOUR STUPID LIST.
WHAT ABOUT YOUR KIDS?

01:51.479 --> 01:53.481
YOU HAVE A FAMILY
TO SUPPORT.

01:55.749 --> 01:58.552
- THOSE AREN'T MY KIDS, JOY.
- THAT DOESN'T MATTER.

01:58.586 --> 02:00.854
THEY HAVE GROWN ACCUSTOMED
TO A CERTAIN QUALITY
OF LIFESTYLE...

02:00.888 --> 02:03.524
THAT YOU PROVIDED FOR 'EM
WITH ALL YOUR CROOKERY.

02:03.557 --> 02:06.794
I TRIED TO GET THEIR NEW DADDY
TO FILL YOUR SHOES, BUT DARNELL
IS NOT CUT OUT FOR CRIME.

02:06.827 --> 02:09.730
[ Video Game Beeping ]

02:12.700 --> 02:14.902
[ Gasps ]

02:19.640 --> 02:22.243
I'M SORRY.
I SHOULDN'T OF DID THAT.

02:22.276 --> 02:25.479
THAT'S OKAY.
ARE YOU HUNGRY?

02:25.513 --> 02:29.350
I THINK I HAVE
A LITTLE CANDY BAR IN HERE.
YOU WANT A LITTLE CANDY BAR?

02:30.851 --> 02:34.422
WHERE'S MY GRANDFATHER'S
CUCKOO CLOCK?

02:34.455 --> 02:36.757
- I PAWNED IT.
- WHAT?

02:36.790 --> 02:40.861
WHAT DO YOU THINK,
CIGARETTES GROW ON TREES?

02:40.894 --> 02:42.963
[ Earl Narrating ]
EXCEPT FOR SCOLIOSIS,

02:42.996 --> 02:46.567
THE ONLY THING MY GRANDFATHER
PASSED DOWN TO ME
WAS THAT CUCKOO CLOCK.

02:46.600 --> 02:50.871
AND I COULDN'T STAND THE THOUGHT
OF MY FAMILY'S ONLY HEIRLOOM
SITTIN' IN A PAWNSHOP.

02:50.904 --> 02:53.574
YOU SURE YOU WANNA GET
GRANDPA'S CUCKOO CLOCK BACK?

02:53.607 --> 02:55.809
THAT THING
ALMOST PUT MY EYE OUT.

02:55.843 --> 02:58.512
WELL, YOU SHOULDN'T
HAVE BEEN SO CLOSE.
YOU KNEW WHAT TIME IT WAS.

02:58.546 --> 03:00.781
HOW MUCH IS IT GONNA COST?

03:00.814 --> 03:03.551
THAT'S AN AWFUL LOT
OF VENDING MACHINE DOUGHNUTS
YOU'RE HOLDING THERE.

03:03.584 --> 03:05.753
I'M GETTIN'
AN EXTRA HUNDRED
FOR ROSIE.

03:05.786 --> 03:10.458
AS LONG AS WE'RE HERE,
I MIGHT AS WELL CROSS
NUMBER 58 OFF MY LIST--

03:10.491 --> 03:13.894
FIXED A HIGH SCHOOL
FOOTBALL GAME.
[ Whistle Blows ]

03:13.927 --> 03:16.397
[ Crowd Cheering ]
HUT!

03:16.430 --> 03:18.666
[ Earl Narrating ]
AFTER SITTING ON THE BENCH
ALL YEAR,

03:18.699 --> 03:23.604
THE COACH TOLD RANDY
HE WAS FINALLY GONNA
GET A CHANCE TO PLAY.

03:23.637 --> 03:27.308
I SAW THIS AS AN OPPORTUNITY
TO MAKE A BET WITH ROSIE,

03:27.341 --> 03:29.443
OUR LOCAL BOOKIE
AND PAWNSHOP OWNER.

03:29.477 --> 03:32.012
I BET A HUNDRED DOLLARS
ON RANDY'S TEAM... TO LOSE.

03:32.045 --> 03:34.582
GOOD LUCK.

03:34.615 --> 03:37.685
OF COURSE
I DIDN'T NEED LUCK.
I HAD RANDY.

03:37.718 --> 03:39.553
2-16! HUT!

03:41.489 --> 03:43.591
[ Crowd Booing ]

03:45.393 --> 03:47.961
[ Crowd Groaning ]

03:47.995 --> 03:51.031
HUT!

03:51.064 --> 03:53.434
[ Man ]
AH, YOU FOOL!
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

03:55.303 --> 03:58.572
[ Jeering ]
GET OUT OF HERE!
GET OUT OF HERE, YOU BUM!

04:00.441 --> 04:04.312
I CAN'T WAIT
TO SEE ROSIE'S FACE
WHEN I PAY HER BACK.

04:05.779 --> 04:08.816
YOU DISGUST ME, EARL HICKEY.
FIXIN' A GAME.

04:08.849 --> 04:12.986
I SHOULD PULL YOU THROUGH
THIS TALKIN' HOLE AND STOMP ON
YOUR SWEATY LITTLE TEA BAG.

04:20.661 --> 04:22.730
WHAT'S UP, ROSIE?
HOW YOU BEEN?

04:24.765 --> 04:28.369
YOU HAD ONE CHANCE
TO FEEL WHAT IT WAS LIKE
TO SCORE A TOUCHDOWN,

04:28.402 --> 04:32.873
AND YA THREW IT ALL AWAY
JUST BECAUSE YOUR WORTHLESS
BROTHER ASKED YOU TO.

04:32.906 --> 04:35.776
[ Earl Narrating ]
THAT WAS TRUE.

04:35.809 --> 04:37.745
[ Whistle Blows ]

04:37.778 --> 04:39.480
HUT!

04:41.915 --> 04:44.885
[ Man ]
RUN! RUN!

04:47.688 --> 04:49.390
BLOCK HIM!

05:06.106 --> 05:08.409
[ Groaning ]

05:08.442 --> 05:11.579
[ Earl Narrating ] MAYBE I
DIDN'T JUST CHEAT THE BOOKIE.
MAYBE I CHEATED RANDY TOO.

05:11.612 --> 05:14.515
I TOOK AWAY HIS ONE CHANCE
TO SCORE A TOUCHDOWN.

05:14.548 --> 05:17.951
RANDY, DO YOU
REGRET THE FACT THAT YOU
NEVER GOT TO FEEL...

05:17.985 --> 05:20.921
WHAT IT'S LIKE
TO SCORE A TOUCHDOWN?

05:20.954 --> 05:24.458
UH, I GUESS
IT WOULD HAVE BEEN COOL
TO GET LIFTED UP BY PEOPLE.

05:24.492 --> 05:29.096
I NEVER BEEN
LIFTED UP BEFORE.
IT LOOKS FUN.

05:29.129 --> 05:31.732
I THINK I HAVE TO PUT YOU
ON MY LIST, RANDY.

05:31.765 --> 05:34.635
I TOOK AWAY YOUR TOUCHDOWN.
I GOTTA GIVE IT BACK.

05:34.668 --> 05:36.637
HOW IN THE WORLD
ARE YOU GONNA DO THAT?

05:36.670 --> 05:38.806
THIS MAY SOUND CRAZY,

05:38.839 --> 05:42.576
BUT I-I THINK YOU HAVE TO
GO BACK TO HIGH SCHOOL.

05:42.610 --> 05:44.845
[ Cuckooing ]

05:46.013 --> 05:48.449
THAT WAS WEIRD.

05:48.482 --> 05:51.785
[ Earl Narrating ] I NEEDED
TO GET RANDY A FAKE BIRTH
CERTIFICATE FOR HIGH SCHOOL.

05:51.819 --> 05:54.622
LUCKILY,
THAT HOMOSEXUAL FELLOW I KNOW
WORKS AT A COPY PLACE.

05:54.655 --> 05:56.624
THANKS FOR DOING THIS,
KENNY.

05:56.657 --> 05:59.393
ARE YOU KIDDING?
THANK YOU FOR HELPING ME
OUT OF THE CLOSET.

05:59.427 --> 06:02.029
I DIDN'T REALIZE THERE
WERE OTHER PEOPLE LIKE ME.

06:02.062 --> 06:05.098
I'VE WORKED WITH BRUCE
FOR YEARS AND DIDN'T KNOW.
OH, YES, YOU WILL COLLATE!

06:08.436 --> 06:10.904
HERE YOU GO.

06:10.938 --> 06:13.441
[ Earl Narrating ]
THE BIRTH CERTIFICATE
LOOKED GREAT.

06:13.474 --> 06:16.677
ALL WE NEEDED WAS A FAKE FATHER
TO SIGN THE PAPERWORK,
AND WE WERE IN.

06:16.710 --> 06:19.547
TRANSFER STUDENT, HUH?

06:19.580 --> 06:22.750
[ Synthesized Voice ]
I TRAVEL A LOT FOR WORK.

06:22.783 --> 06:25.419
[ Earl Narrating ]
WITH FOOTBALL SEASON
ALMOST OVER,

06:25.453 --> 06:28.088
I WANTED TO MAKE SURE RANDY
GOT A CHANCE TO PLAY,

06:28.121 --> 06:31.124
SO I PICKED THE SCHOOL
WITH THE WORST TEAM
IN THE LEAGUE.

06:35.128 --> 06:37.130
[ Inhaler Squirting ]

06:49.877 --> 06:51.912
HOW WAS YOUR
FIRST DAY AT SCHOOL?

06:51.945 --> 06:54.715
GREAT. I REALLY ENJOYED
SCIENCE CLASS.

06:54.748 --> 06:57.751
DID YOU KNOW
THAT BEFORE WE WERE HUMANS,
WE WERE MONKEYS?

06:57.785 --> 07:00.721
REALLY? WHAT WERE WE
BEFORE MONKEYS?

07:00.754 --> 07:04.191
I DON'T KNOW.
I CAN'T EVEN REMEMBER
BEING A MONKEY.

07:06.794 --> 07:08.862
WHERE'S MY CAR?
WHAT?

07:08.896 --> 07:11.999
I PARKED MY CAR
RIGHT HERE.

07:12.032 --> 07:14.735
SOMEONE STOLE MY CAR.

07:14.768 --> 07:18.071
MY MONEY. MY MONEY
WAS IN THE CAR. RANDY,
MY MONEY WAS IN THE CAR.

07:18.105 --> 07:20.240
WHO'D WANNA
STEAL YOUR CAR?

07:20.273 --> 07:23.811
IT'S A PIECE OF CRAP
WITH "ASSTRONAUT"
PAINTED ON THE SIDE.

07:26.914 --> 07:28.782
JOY.

07:37.658 --> 07:41.695
- WHERE IS IT, JOY?
- WHY DON'T YOU ASK THE GUYS
DOWN AT IMPOUND?

07:41.729 --> 07:43.864
YOU HAD MY CAR TOWED?

07:43.897 --> 07:47.668
YUP. MAYBE IF YOU GAVE ME
SOME OF THAT LOTTO MONEY,
I'D FIND BETTER THINGS TO DO.

07:47.701 --> 07:50.203
[ Earl Narrating ]
IT WAS AT THAT POINT
I REALIZED JOY HAD NO IDEA...

07:50.237 --> 07:53.240
THAT MY MONEY
WAS ACTUALLY IN THE CAR.

07:53.273 --> 07:56.209
HEY, EARL. JOY HAD NO IDEA
THAT YOUR LOTTO MONEY
WAS IN YOUR CAR.

08:09.957 --> 08:13.561
OW! OH!
[ Hisses ]

08:13.594 --> 08:17.531
I BUSTED OPEN
MY RUG BURN.

08:17.565 --> 08:19.733
[ Earl Narrating ]
JOY'S FALL BOUGHT US
A LITTLE TIME,

08:19.767 --> 08:22.169
BUT GETTING THE CAR
WASN'T GONNA BE EASY.

08:22.202 --> 08:24.972
IT SEEMS I OWED SOME MONEY
ON UNPAID PARKING TICKETS.

08:25.005 --> 08:27.708
$3,000?
THAT'S WHAT I SAID.

08:29.777 --> 08:33.080
[ Earl Narrating ]
I KNEW I COULD PAY HIM IF I
COULD JUST GET TO THE CAR,

08:33.113 --> 08:36.784
BUT THESE AREN'T THE KIND
OF GUYS YOU WANNA LET KNOW YOU
HAVE CHANGE IN YOUR ASHTRAY,

08:36.817 --> 08:39.587
MUCH LESS $100,000
UNDER YOUR FRONT SEAT.

08:39.620 --> 08:42.255
WHAT'S UP
WITH THE FOOTBALL?

08:42.289 --> 08:45.926
I PLAY FOR NORTHWESTERN HIGH.
I'M GONNA SCORE A TOUCHDOWN.

08:45.959 --> 08:48.929
NORTHWESTERN HIGH?
WHAT ARE YOU,
IN THE 17th GRADE?

08:48.962 --> 08:52.199
EXCUSE ME, SIR.
I'M HERE TO PICK UP MY CAR.

08:52.232 --> 08:56.236
NOPE! IT'S NOT HER CAR.
THAT'S MY CAR.
MY NAME'S ON THE TITLE TOO.

08:56.269 --> 08:58.906
I DON'T GIVE
A RAT'S ASPIRIN BOTTLE
WHOSE DAMN CAR IT IS.

08:58.939 --> 09:02.576
I'M GONNA GIVE IT
TO WHOEVER GIVES ME $3,000.

09:02.610 --> 09:05.613
SIR, CAN I HAVE
THIS MAGAZINE
FOR A COLLAGE?

09:05.646 --> 09:08.048
ONE OF THE CHEERLEADERS
WAS OUT SICK TODAY,

09:08.081 --> 09:10.150
AND WE'RE GONNA
DECORATE HER LOCKER.

09:10.183 --> 09:12.820
[ Earl Narrating ]
I KNEW NEITHER JOY OR I
WOULD BE ABLE...

09:12.853 --> 09:15.889
TO COME UP WITH $3,000
WITHOUT SELLING A KIDNEY,

09:15.923 --> 09:18.959
SO I CONCENTRATED MY EFFORTS
ON SOMEHOW GETTING TO THE CAR.

09:18.992 --> 09:21.128
I DON'T KNOW, EARL.

09:21.161 --> 09:23.897
MAYBE WE SHOULD THINK
OF ANOTHER WAY. I MEAN,
ELECTRICITY HURTS.

09:23.931 --> 09:27.167
I USED TO SNEAK MY CAR OUT
OF HERE ALL THE TIME. THEY ONLY
TURN THIS THING ON AT NIGHT.

09:32.940 --> 09:35.008
SEE?

09:35.042 --> 09:37.678
COME ON.
LET'S GET THAT MONEY.

09:43.183 --> 09:45.052
WAIT FOR IT.

09:48.088 --> 09:50.357
- NOW.
- [ Screams ]

09:50.390 --> 09:53.827
[ Thudding ]
[ Earl Narrating ] WHILE I WAS
BUSY TRYING TO GET TO MY CAR,

09:53.861 --> 09:55.963
JOY WAS TRYING
TO GET A LOAN FOR $3,000.

09:58.031 --> 10:02.135
HEY, BABY.
DARNELL, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING IN HERE?

10:02.169 --> 10:05.305
I TOLD YOU
TO WAIT IN THE CAR.
IT'S HOT OUT THERE.

10:05.338 --> 10:07.374
BABY, I'M TRYING TO GET
A LOAN HERE, OKAY?

10:07.407 --> 10:09.710
LOOK, YOU KNOW
I DON'T SEE COLOR,

10:09.743 --> 10:12.312
BUT THESE PEOPLE ARE NEVER
GONNA GIVE ME $3,000...

10:12.345 --> 10:16.183
IF THEY SEE ME HERE
WITH A BLACK MAN, OKAY?

10:16.216 --> 10:19.953
DARNELL, IT'S NOT ME!
IT'S AMERICA.
I DON'T MAKE THE RULES.

10:29.429 --> 10:32.232
SO, THEY TELL ME YOU'RE
LOOKING FOR A LOAN.

10:32.265 --> 10:36.369
YEAH. YOU KNOW WHAT?
I LEFT SOMETHING IN THE CAR.
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

10:39.472 --> 10:42.409
WE REALLY ONLY NEED THE MONEY
FOR, LIKE, AN HOUR OR TWO.

10:44.111 --> 10:47.214
[ Whispers ]
SAY SOMETHIN' BLACK.

10:47.247 --> 10:50.050
[ Earl Narrating ] JOY DIDN'T
REALIZE THAT IT DOESN'T MATTER
IF YOU'RE BLACK OR WHITE.

10:50.083 --> 10:53.320
YOU CAN'T BORROW MONEY
AGAINST A RENTED
1972 TRAILER...

10:53.353 --> 10:55.455
WITH A DOCUMENTED
CARBON MONOXIDE LEAK.

10:55.488 --> 10:58.125
I'M SORRY.

11:03.764 --> 11:06.399
- NICE PULL, BROTHER.
- RIGHT ON.

11:09.837 --> 11:13.073
HEY, EARL?
I NEED $20 TO ENTER
THE SCIENCE FAIR.

11:13.106 --> 11:15.342
RANDY, ALL MY MONEY'S
IN THE CAR.

11:15.375 --> 11:18.245
BESIDES,
YOU'RE GOING TO HIGH SCHOOL
TO SCORE A TOUCHDOWN,

11:18.278 --> 11:20.814
NOT DECORATE LOCKERS
AND ENTER THE SCIENCE FAIR.

11:20.848 --> 11:23.717
COME ON.
IT'S ONLY $20.

11:23.751 --> 11:25.953
HE'S ALREADY GROWING
HIS POTATO.

11:27.320 --> 11:30.123
JUST PUT THE BOOKS DOWN
AND HELP ME THINK.

11:30.157 --> 11:33.727
IF WE DON'T FIGURE OUT A WAY
TO BREAK INTO THE IMPOUND YARD
AND GET MY MONEY,

11:33.761 --> 11:35.362
WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO
EAT THAT POTATO.

11:35.395 --> 11:38.732
OH, HEY, EARL.
HOW ABOUT THIS?

11:38.766 --> 11:41.334
IT'S CALLED
A TROJAN HORSE.

11:41.368 --> 11:44.938
[ Earl Narrating ] AND THERE
IT WAS-- A GREAT IDEA THAT WE
NEVER WOULD HAVE FOUND...

11:44.972 --> 11:47.307
IF I HADN'T MADE RANDY
GO BACK TO HIGH SCHOOL.

11:48.909 --> 11:51.078
KARMA STRIKES AGAIN.

11:51.111 --> 11:54.247
[ Earl Narrating ]
INSTEAD OF A WOODEN HORSE,
I WAS GONNA USE A CAR.

11:54.281 --> 11:58.085
I CALLED THE ONLY GUY
I KNEW THAT HAD ONE THAT
ACTUALLY WORKED-- KENNY.

11:58.118 --> 12:01.755
I'LL JUST HIDE IN THE TRUNK,
AND YOU PARK THE CAR
IN FRONT OF A HYDRANT.

12:01.789 --> 12:04.391
ONCE I'M TOWED
INTO THE IMPOUND,
I'LL HOP OUT, GET MY MONEY,

12:04.424 --> 12:07.094
HEAD ON OVER TO
THE HIGH SCHOOL AND WATCH
RANDY SCORE A TOUCHDOWN.

12:07.127 --> 12:09.262
SOUNDS LIKE
A SOLID PLAN, EARL.

12:09.296 --> 12:11.832
[ Earl Narrating ]
KENNY'S A GOOD GUY,
BUT, TO BE HONEST,

12:11.865 --> 12:14.034
HIS FRIEND MADE ME
A LITTLE UNCOMFORTABLE.

12:14.067 --> 12:16.804
THIS IS SO EXCITING!

12:19.239 --> 12:21.341
LET ME JUST
GET IN THE CAR.

12:33.586 --> 12:35.789
DAMN. I'M TOO BIG.

12:35.823 --> 12:38.258
- I'LL DO IT.
- REALLY?

12:38.291 --> 12:41.795
AFTER EVERYTHING
YOU'VE DONE FOR ME,
IT'S THE LEAST I CAN DO.

12:41.829 --> 12:44.397
WOW. THANKS, KENNY.
ARE YOU SURE YOU CAN FIT
IN THE TRUNK?

12:44.431 --> 12:46.499
I'VE SEEN HIM FIT
INTO A TRUNK.

12:46.533 --> 12:48.501
[ Giggling ]
STOP IT.
YOU STOP IT.

12:48.535 --> 12:50.203
YOU STOP IT.
YOU STOP IT!

12:50.237 --> 12:52.305
YOU STOP IT!
YOU STOP IT!

12:52.339 --> 12:56.109
WHY DON'T WE ALL STOP IT, OKAY?
LET'S SHUT DOWN THE HORSEPLAY.

12:59.212 --> 13:02.515
ALL RIGHT. ALL RIGHT.
ONCE THE CAR IS IN THE IMPOUND,
HOP OUT, GET MY MONEY...

13:02.549 --> 13:05.252
AND MEET ME
AT THE FOOTBALL GAME.

13:05.285 --> 13:08.321
[ Earl Narrating ]
WHILE I WAS TRYING
TO GET THE CAR,

13:08.355 --> 13:11.124
RANDY WAS GETTING PSYCHED.

13:11.158 --> 13:14.127
ARE YOU READY?
I'M READY.
ARE YOU READY?

13:14.161 --> 13:16.830
I'M READY. YOU READY?

13:16.864 --> 13:19.066
I'M READY!
ARE YOU READY?
OW.

13:19.099 --> 13:20.968
[ Whimpers ]

13:21.001 --> 13:24.037
[ Earl Narrating ]
WHILE RANDY WAS
GETTING PSYCHED,

13:24.071 --> 13:27.274
JOY WAS STILL TRYING TO
GET HER HANDS ON $3,000.

13:29.877 --> 13:33.180
I SOLD ALMOST EVERYTHING WE OWN,
AND ALL I GOT WAS $1,500.

13:33.213 --> 13:36.884
- THAT'S NOT ENOUGH.
- I DON'T KNOW WHERE WE'RE GONNA
GET ALL THIS MONEY FROM.

13:41.621 --> 13:43.590
WATCH MY BACK.

13:54.667 --> 13:56.469
[ Mouthing Words ]

13:58.538 --> 14:01.875
[ Earl Narrating ]
AS FOR MY PLAN, THE TROJAN
HORSE WAS ON ITS WAY.

14:01.909 --> 14:04.611
ONLY, INSTEAD OF A HORSE STUFFED
WITH A BUNCH OF GREEKS,

14:04.644 --> 14:08.581
WE HAD A LE CAR STUFFED
WITH ONE TINY GAY.

14:08.615 --> 14:11.318
WHICH MEANT I WAS FREE
TO ENJOY THE GAME.

14:11.351 --> 14:15.022
AND I WANTED RANDY
TO HAVE A LOT OF SUPPORT,
SO CATALINA CAME TOO.

14:15.055 --> 14:17.357
I EVEN INVITED
HIS FAKE DAD.

14:17.390 --> 14:20.928
[ Synthesized Voice ]
PUSH 'EM BACK.
PUSH 'EM BACK. WAY BACK!

14:30.403 --> 14:33.106
YOU CAN STOP NOW.

14:33.140 --> 14:36.343
STUPID GUY
AT THE RECYCLE CENTER ONLY
GAVE ME EIGHT DOLLARS...

14:36.376 --> 14:39.146
FOR THAT WHOLE CART
FULL OF CANS.

14:39.179 --> 14:42.015
- WE'LL NEVER MAKE
ENOUGH MONEY THIS WAY.
- YOU THINK?

14:42.049 --> 14:44.985
THESE CANS ARE
JUST TOO DAMN SMALL.

14:45.018 --> 14:47.120
THEY PAY BY THE POUND.
WE NEED HEAVIER CANS.

14:50.690 --> 14:53.226
HEY, WHAT IS THIS THINGY
MADE OUT OF?

15:06.206 --> 15:11.144
[ Grunts, Groans ]

15:11.178 --> 15:14.114
[ Earl Narrating ] RANDY WAS
HAVING MORE TROUBLE ON THE FIELD
THAN I HAD ANTICIPATED.

15:14.147 --> 15:16.483
I THINK ALL THOSE YEARS
OF SLEEPING ALL DAY
AND DRINKING ALL NIGHT...

15:16.516 --> 15:18.385
HAD CAUGHT UP WITH HIM.

15:20.453 --> 15:22.555
HE LOOKS WOBBLY.

15:22.589 --> 15:25.492
KEEP YOUR CHIN UP, RANDY!
YOU CAN DO THIS!

15:25.525 --> 15:28.395
I NEED YOU TO SCORE, BUDDY.

15:35.168 --> 15:37.670
WHERE THE HELL IS KENNY?

15:37.704 --> 15:40.240
[ Barking, Snarling ]

15:40.273 --> 15:42.642
[ Earl Narrating ]
UNFORTUNATELY FOR KENNY--
[ Gasps ] HELP!

15:42.675 --> 15:45.012
THE AFTERSHAVE HE WAS WEARING
ATTRACTED DOBERMANS.
HELP!

15:45.045 --> 15:47.714
[ Announcer ] WITH 12 SECONDS
LEFT ON THE CLOCK HERE
IN THE FOURTH QUARTER,

15:47.747 --> 15:50.617
BESIDE THIS RUN,
THE ROCKETS--

15:50.650 --> 15:53.120
THIS IS HIS LAST CHANCE
TO SCORE.

15:53.153 --> 15:57.190
GIVE ME THE BALL.
I'LL GET IT IN THE END ZONE.
I HAVE TO. READY?

15:57.224 --> 15:59.292
[ All ]
BREAK!

15:59.326 --> 16:01.028
COME ON, RANDY!

16:04.597 --> 16:08.035
ON THREE. HUT, HUT! GO!

16:30.190 --> 16:32.759
[ Crowd Groaning ]

16:34.494 --> 16:37.064
[ Horn Blows ]
[ Man Shouting ]

16:40.133 --> 16:42.469
[ Man ]
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

17:00.253 --> 17:03.290
[ Earl Narrating ]
I FELT HORRIBLE.
I HAD SET RANDY UP TO FAIL.

17:03.323 --> 17:06.493
I FELT LIKE I TOOK AWAY
HIS TOUCHDOWN ALL OVER AGAIN.

17:06.526 --> 17:11.098
I CAN'T FIND HIM ANYWHERE.
HE MUST HAVE BEEN SO UPSET,
HE WALKED HOME.

17:11.131 --> 17:15.135
[ Horn Honking ]
HEY, EARL HICKEY!

17:15.168 --> 17:18.638
I RAISED THE $3,000.
WHERE'S YOUR KARMA NOW, DUMMY?

17:20.340 --> 17:24.377
- HEY, EARL.
- HEY, CRAB MAN.

17:24.411 --> 17:26.146
[ Tires Screeching ]

17:29.416 --> 17:33.320
[ Earl Narrating ] I KNEW AS
SOON AS JOY GOT TO THAT IMPOUND
YARD, MY LIFE WOULD BE RUINED.

17:33.353 --> 17:36.089
WITHOUT MY HUNDRED GRAND,
I'D HAVE TO GET A JOB,

17:36.123 --> 17:38.858
AND I WOULDN'T HAVE TIME
TO CROSS THINGS OFF MY LIST.

17:38.891 --> 17:41.528
SO, I STARTED RUNNING.

17:43.263 --> 17:47.734
AND I RAN
AS FAST AS I COULD...

17:47.767 --> 17:49.669
FOR AS LONG AS I COULD.

17:55.242 --> 17:58.378
BUT EVENTUALLY, ALL THOSE YEARS
OF SLEEPING ALL DAY
AND DRINKING ALL NIGHT...

17:58.411 --> 18:00.313
CAUGHT UP WITH ME.

18:04.651 --> 18:08.121
THE MEN IN YOUR FAMILY
DON'T WORK OUT A LOT,
DO THEY?

18:08.155 --> 18:12.292
WE NEVER GOT CAUGHT UP
IN THE WHOLE PHYSICAL
FITNESS CRAZE, NO.

18:12.325 --> 18:15.362
[ Earl Narrating ]
IT WAS BAD ENOUGH THAT JOY WAS
ON HER WAY TO STEAL MY MONEY,

18:15.395 --> 18:19.332
BUT I WAS ALSO STARTING TO
REGRET WEARING FLANNEL BOXERS
ON SUCH A HOT DAY.

18:19.366 --> 18:22.569
I CAN'T BELIEVE ALL
MY MONEY'S GONNA BE GONE.
MY LIFE IS OVER.

18:22.602 --> 18:25.138
WHERE I GREW UP,
WE HAVE THESE THINGS
CALLED BANKS.

18:25.172 --> 18:26.839
[ Horn Honking ]

18:30.843 --> 18:33.213
YOU TWO NEED A RIDE?

18:33.246 --> 18:36.583
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING?
HOW'D YOU GET MY CAR?

18:38.251 --> 18:41.621
I PAID THE $3,000
TO GET IT OUT.
WHAT? HOW?

18:41.654 --> 18:44.457
I FIXED THE GAME AGAIN.
I FUMBLED THAT BALL
ON PURPOSE.

18:44.491 --> 18:47.527
AND THIS TIME, INSTEAD OF
BETTING A HUNDRED DOLLARS,
I BET 3,000.

18:47.560 --> 18:50.497
SO YOU WERE JUST FAKING IT
WHEN YOU LOOKED SO TIRED
ON THE FIELD?

18:50.530 --> 18:52.765
NO, THAT WAS REAL.
I THREW UP FOUR TIMES.

18:52.799 --> 18:54.834
WAIT. WHY DIDN'T YOU
TELL ME ABOUT THIS?

18:54.867 --> 18:58.371
'CAUSE I KNEW
YOU AND YOUR KARMA LIST
WOULDN'T LET ME DO IT.

18:58.405 --> 19:01.441
WHAT'S THE MATTER?
AREN'T YOU HAPPY?

19:01.474 --> 19:04.644
NO, I'M HAPPY.
I'M HAPPY I GOT THE MONEY BACK,
BUT I DID IT AGAIN.

19:04.677 --> 19:07.880
I FORCED HIM TO GIVE UP
HIS TOUCHDOWN. I CAN'T
CROSS IT OFF THE LIST.

19:07.914 --> 19:09.882
EARL, YOU DIDN'T
MAKE ME DO THIS.

19:09.916 --> 19:12.952
I DID IT BECAUSE
YOU'RE MY BROTHER
AND I WANTED TO.

19:12.985 --> 19:15.622
I CAN MAKE MY OWN DECISIONS.
I'M NOT AN IDIOT.

19:15.655 --> 19:18.558
BUT DON'T YOU WANNA KNOW
WHAT IT FEELS LIKE
TO SCORE A TOUCHDOWN?

19:18.591 --> 19:21.294
I'M PRETTY SURE IT'S ABOUT
THE SAME FEELING I GOT...

19:21.328 --> 19:24.697
WHEN I DROVE UP AND SAW
THE SMILE ON YOUR FACE.

19:24.731 --> 19:27.567
WELL, THERE'S ONLY
ONE THING LEFT TO DO.

19:27.600 --> 19:29.802
CATALINA.

19:31.671 --> 19:33.806
[ Chuckling ]
WHOO-HOO!
PUT ME DOWN.

19:33.840 --> 19:36.243
I DON'T LIKE IT!
I DON'T LIKE IT!

19:36.276 --> 19:38.945
[ Earl Narrating ]
FIRST THING WE DID THE NEXT DAY
WAS PAY ROSIE BACK...

19:38.978 --> 19:41.548
THE THREE GRAND WE WON
BY FIXING THE GAME.

19:41.581 --> 19:44.751
NEEDLESS TO SAY,
SHE WASN'T TOO HAPPY ABOUT IT.

19:44.784 --> 19:46.886
YOU'RE PATHETIC,
EARL HICKEY!

19:46.919 --> 19:48.888
[ Earl Narrating ]
AS FOR KENNY,

19:48.921 --> 19:51.891
HE EVENTUALLY
MADE ENOUGH NOISE THAT SOMEONE
CAME AND RESCUED HIM.

19:51.924 --> 19:56.896
AS IT TURNED OUT,
HIS DRAKKAR NOIR ATTRACTED
MORE THAN JUST THE DOGS.

19:56.929 --> 19:59.566
KENNY TOLD ME LATER
THAT HE AND HIS NEW FRIEND...

19:59.599 --> 20:02.402
SPENT A LOVELY WEEKEND TOGETHER
IN WINE COUNTRY.

20:02.435 --> 20:05.438
I WAS JUST GLAD TO HEAR
BRUCE WAS NO LONGER
IN THE PICTURE.

20:07.307 --> 20:09.809
AND NOW THAT I HAD
MY MONEY BACK,

20:09.842 --> 20:13.446
I WAS ABLE TO GIVE RANDY
20 BUCKS TO ROUND OUT
HIS HIGH SCHOOL EXPERIENCE.

20:23.590 --> 20:26.559
"PARTICIPANT." NICE.

20:28.295 --> 20:31.298
[ Earl Narrating ]
AS FOR JOY,
WHAT HAPPENED TO HER?

20:31.331 --> 20:33.900
THAT'S THE BEST PART
OF THE WHOLE STORY.
I'M SO EXCITED!

20:33.933 --> 20:37.370
SNIFF THIS.
WE'RE GONNA BE RICH.
[ Laughing ]

20:37.404 --> 20:40.373
[ Gasps ]
[ Tires Screeching ]

20:40.407 --> 20:43.443
[ Crashing ]

20:49.816 --> 20:53.886
[ Angry Grunting ]

20:53.920 --> 20:56.656
HOW AM I GONNA GET THE CAR
OUT RIGHT NOW?

20:56.689 --> 20:58.758
DARNELL, HOW AM I SUPPOSED
TO GET THE CAR OUT?

20:58.791 --> 21:00.793
[ Earl Narrating ]
KARMA. YOU GOTTA LOVE IT.
